# 8. 撮影を終えて

TV Crew: That's a wrap! Thank you all very much for your hard work!
Minori: Thank you!
Airi: Phew... A lot happened, but we somehow managed to make it through!
Minori: Yeah! And it was great how the audience knew what we were talking about while we were trying those snacks!
Shizuku: Hehe. I'm so glad we shared those with them.
Haruka: There's also a lot I'd like to talk about...
Haruka: But we should start preparing for our next engagement.
Airi: The interview for that house...
Minori: Oh, I almost forgot! It's at eight, right? What time is it now...?
Minori: S-Seven?! It's already this late?!
Shizuku: We did have quite a bit of a delay, but we may still be able to make it in time.
Crew Member: The audience will now be exiting the studio!
Yuika: Oh, I should go see them out.
MYU: Me too! I wanna hear what they thought of the show!
Minori: Oh...
Haruka: They're leaving... We should also say goodbye to them.
Airi: Yeah... But staying means running late for our interview.
Airi: Getting approved was already supposed to be hard, so being late would probably mean an instant fail.
Shizuku: Which means we'd have to find a new house. But...
Minori: I still want to see them out.
Minori: They had to wait so long because of that delay, so I feel we should thank them one last time.
Minori: Oh, also... I wanna thank the crew and other personalities for all their hard work...
Airi: Me too...
Shizuku: Me three! I was just thinking the same thing.
Haruka: We'll need to apologize to the landlady and give a thorough explanation of what happened...
Haruka: But for now, let's focus on the task at hand.
Minori: Oh...
Shizuku: I'll ask Saito to let Ms. Kawanishi know that we'll be running late.
Minori: Thanks, Shizuku...!
Minori: Anyway, let's head on over!
Crew Member: How great were they? Not only were they willing to give the crew a hand, they kept the morale of the audience and personalities up.
Kuromiya: Yeah, they did such an amazing job...
Kuromiya: I guess idols are idols no matter where they go, huh?
Crew Member: What do you mean?
Kuromiya: You haven't heard that before? It's something a legendary idol once said that everyone in the business hears by word of mouth.
Kuromiya: The stage isn't the only place where idols spread hope.
Kuromiya: And I think those girls are well on their way to embodying that ideal.
Elderly Lady: Oh, I see...
Elderly Lady: No, I should be apologizing for always causing you so much trouble. Please don't ever hesitate to contact me.
Elderly Lady: Phew... At least I don't have to rush back now.
Audience Member Ａ: Man, MORE MORE JUMP! was so awesome!
Audience Member Ｂ: Yeah, they really were! I got kinda bored during that delay, but they came over to talk to us to pass the time. And they were there to say goodbye to us.
Audience Member Ｂ: I'm starting to really like them! I might check out their channel when I get home.
Elderly Lady: Oh... They saw things through.
Elderly Lady: Which means they just might have what it takes...
Rin: <What you all did at the shoot was so awesome!>
Miku: <Yes, it was! I still can't believe you were able to find such a wonderful solution to that problem!>
Airi: Yeah, but... Minori deserves most of the credit for that.
Shizuku: I agree. It was very cool of you to do all that for the audience, Minori! You set a wonderful example for us...
Minori: No, I should be the one thanking all of you. I'm honored to be receiving praise from such veteran idols...!
Airi: Still... It's too bad that we're not getting that house.
Len: <Yeah, that is kinda unfortunate... It was a nice place, and you girls were so excited about it too.>
Haruka: We could've planned better. Yes, we did give ourselves plenty of time, but scheduling both things for the same day may not have been such a great idea.
Shizuku: Right... We should've asked to see if we could do the interview on a different day after we heard from Saito about this shoot.
Airi: To be fair, if the landlady was as picky as advertised, then we might've gotten rejected just for asking to reschedule.
KAITO: <But I wouldn't worry too much about this! I'm sure you'll find another nice property.>
Luka: <He's right. You'll find one as long as you keep looking.>
Minori: Right! Then, we'll call Ms. Kawanishi again and...
Minori: Huh? Is someone calling?
Shizuku: It's Saito. This could be about that house.
Shizuku: Hello? This is Hinomori... I'm so sorry, Saito. Our shoot just ended.
Shizuku: What...?!
Haruka: Is something wrong?
Shizuku: F-For whatever reason...
Shizuku: The landlady has apparently taken a liking to us, and she'd like to see us tomorrow if possible...
Minori: What?!
Minori: O-Okay, we're here as requested...
Minori: B-But is this really gonna happen?! What if the landlady gets mad at us for no-showing yesterday...?
Haruka: If she asked to see us just for that reason, then we may have a tough time dealing with her...
Haruka: But it's our fault for not making the interview, and we already intended to apologize in person. So, let's just tell her how we feel.
Minori: R-Right...! Then, I'm ringing the bell...!
Airi: Okay...
Minori: Here goes nothing!
???: <Hello...?>
Minori: Uhh... P-P-P-P-Pardon us! We're MORE MORE JUMP! We have an appointment to...
???: <Excellent, you're here. Just give me one second.>
Minori: O-Okay...!
Haruka: She seems nicer than we initially expected...
Airi: Yeah, but hold on...
Shizuku: That voice sounded so familiar...
???: Thank you for waiting. I appreciate you coming all this way.
Haruka: Huh...?
Minori: Y-You're...
Elderly Lady: Hello. I'm the landlady of this property.
Minori: I-It's you...!
Elderly Lady: It's so nice to see you again, Minori.
Minori: W-Wait a second... If you're the landlady, then that means you're going to interview us...?
Minori: No, first! We need to apologize for what happened yesterday.
Minori: I'm sure you're already aware, but we had a shoot yesterday and...
Elderly Lady: Hehe. Don't worry. I understand why you had to cancel.
Elderly Lady: More importantly, I asked you to come today because I wanted to meet all of you in person.
Elderly Lady: Since you're going to be my new tenants.
Shizuku: ...! Does that mean...?
Minori: You're approving us...? We get to rent this house?!
Haruka: But why...?
Elderly Lady: Firstly, I owe you for helping me the other day.
Elderly Lady: Secondly, I realized after talking to Minori that you all just might have what it takes to make your dreams come true. In other words, you're the ideal tenants for this place.
Minori: After talking to me...?
Elderly Lady: So, here are the keys. You're welcome to start moving in at any time.
Elderly Lady: Also, I'm sure you've already heard that I live here on the first floor, so please feel free to let me know if you run into any trouble.
Minori: Oh...
Minori: Thank you so much! I'm so happy since I'd really fallen in love with this house...!
Shizuku: Me too...! We promise to take good care of it!
Airi: Yeah, we did help her when she fell that time... But is that really a reason to approve us?
Haruka: I'm not sure. Still, she seemed to indicate that talking to Minori played a key role...
Airi: Yeah, that's what it sounded like.
Haruka: People who can make their dreams come true...
Airi: Although, I'm not sure she realizes...
Haruka: Hehe. Probably not.
Airi: (Also...)
Airi: (It didn't occur to me when we first ran into her, but I can't shake this feeling that I've seen her before somewhere...)
Airi: (But I can't think of when. Or I'm just imagining things...)
Haruka: In any case, we can finally establish our new home base... The MORE MORE HOUSE.
Airi: Hehe. Yeah. Which means...
Airi: We're going to spread hope to tons of people from here moving forward!
Minori: (We're gonna do so much stuff together here.)
Minori: (Streams, editing, meetings, practice... Right here in this house.)
Minori: (Right...)
Minori: (Others left behind those scratches as they were pursuing their dreams.)
Minori: (And now I... We're also gonna do everything we can and leave our mark on this place...)
Minori: (Lots of things are probably gonna happen. Some fun, some not so fun...)
Minori: (But...)
Minori: (As long as I have them... As long as we get to be together like this, we should be able to handle anything that comes our way.)
Minori: Everyone! Let's keep doing our best together!
Haruka: What's gotten into you all of a sudden?
Airi: That's our Minori for you.
